<REFENTRY ID="baselib-joystickio-2"> <REFMETA>
<REFENTRYTITLE>joystickio</REFENTRYTITLE>
<REFMISCINFO>Base Libraries</REFMISCINFO>
</REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>joystickio
</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
joystick ioctl commands
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<DATE>23 March 2005</DATE>
</REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<FUNCSYNOPSIS>
<FUNCSYNOPSISINFO>
#include &lt;linux/joystick.h&gt;
</FUNCSYNOPSISINFO>
<FUNCPROTOTYPE>
 <FUNCDEF>int 
  <FUNCTION>ioctl</FUNCTION></FUNCDEF>
 <PARAMDEF>int 
  <PARAMETER><REPLACEABLE>fd</REPLACEABLE></PARAMETER></PARAMDEF>
 <PARAMDEF>int 
  <PARAMETER><REPLACEABLE>request</REPLACEABLE></PARAMETER></PARAMDEF>
 <PARAMDEF>char *
  <PARAMETER><REPLACEABLE>argp</REPLACEABLE></PARAMETER></PARAMDEF>
</FUNCPROTOTYPE>
</FUNCSYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<REFSECT1INFO>
<DATE>23 March 2005</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<PARA>
Joystick <function>ioctl</function> commands are a subset of the 
<FUNCTION>ioctl</FUNCTION> calls, which can perform a variety of 
functions on sockets. <PARAMETER>fd</PARAMETER> shall contain 
the value of a file descriptor that was created with the 
<FUNCTION>open</FUNCTION>.
</PARA>
<PARA>
The following values for <parameter>request</parameter>
are accepted:
</PARA>
<VARIABLELIST>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
JSIOCGVERSION
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
Gets the version of the underlying driver.
<PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER> shall point to a
32 bit integer.  The return value has the major, minor and revision values
encoded in the 32 bit integer as described by the following example.  A return value of 0x01020f coresponds to driver version 1.2.15.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>


<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
JSIOCGAXES
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
Gets the number of axes supported by the underlying driver.
<PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER> shall point to a 8 bit integer. 
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>


<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
JSIOCGBUTTONS
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
Gets the number of buttons supported by the underlying driver.
<PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER> shall point to a
8 bit integer.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>


<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
JSIOCGNAME(len)
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
Gets the identifying string of the underlying driver.
<PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER> shall point to a
character array at least <PARAMETER>len</PARAMETER> octets in length.
</PARA>
<PARA>
If the identifying string of the driver is longer than <PARAMETER>len</PARAMETER>, <SYMBOL>JSIOCGNAME</SYMBOL> shall return EFAULT.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Return Value
</TITLE>
<PARA>
On success, if <parameter>request</parameter> is
<TOKEN>JSIOCGNAME</TOKEN>, a non-negative integer shall be returned.
If request is not <TOKEN>JSIOCGNAME</TOKEN>, on success 
<RETURNVALUE>0</RETURNVALUE> is returned. 
On error, <RETURNVALUE>-1</RETURNVALUE> is returned and
the global variable <VARNAME>errno</VARNAME> is set appropriately.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Errors
</TITLE>
<VARIABLELIST>
<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
EBADF  
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
<PARAMETER>fd</PARAMETER> is not a valid descriptor.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
EFAULT 
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
<PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER> references an inaccessible memory area.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>
EINVAL 
</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
Either <PARAMETER>request</PARAMETER> or <PARAMETER>argp</PARAMETER>
is invalid.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

</VARIABLELIST>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
